{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"Why bother?"},{"time":4600,"text":"The game is rigged."},{"time":6240,"text":"My vote won't count."},{"time":8720,"text":"The choices are terrible."},{"time":10840,"text":"Voting is for suckers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":13280,"text":"Perhaps you've thought\nsome of these things."},{"time":15440,"text":"Perhaps you've even said them."},{"time":17520,"text":"And if so, you wouldn't be alone,\nand you wouldn't be entirely wrong."},{"time":21880,"text":"The game of public policy today\nis rigged in many ways."},{"time":26080,"text":"How else would more than half\nof federal tax breaks"},{"time":30080,"text":"flow up to the wealthiest\nfive percent of Americans?"},{"time":33360,"text":"And our choices indeed are often terrible."},{"time":36360,"text":"For many people\nacross the political spectrum,"},{"time":38560,"text":"Exhibit A is the 2016\npresidential election."},{"time":42760,"text":"But in any year, you can look\nup and down the ballot"},{"time":45320,"text":"and find plenty to be uninspired about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":49560,"text":"But in spite of all this,\nI still believe voting matters."},{"time":53000,"text":"And crazy as it may sound,"},{"time":54920,"text":"I believe we can revive the joy of voting."},{"time":57960,"text":"Today, I want to talk\nabout how we can do that, and why."}]},{"cues":[{"time":62680,"text":"There used to be a time\nin American history when voting was fun,"},{"time":66280,"text":"when it was much more than just\na grim duty to show up at the polls."},{"time":70080,"text":"That time is called\n\"most of American history.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":72520,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":73960,"text":"From the Revolution\nto the Civil Rights Era,"},{"time":76960,"text":"the United States had a vibrant,"},{"time":78560,"text":"robustly participatory\nand raucous culture of voting."},{"time":83480,"text":"It was street theater, open-air debates,\nfasting and feasting and toasting,"},{"time":87640,"text":"parades and bonfires."},{"time":89720,"text":"During the 19th century,\nimmigrants and urban political machines"},{"time":93280,"text":"helped fuel this culture of voting."},{"time":95600,"text":"That culture grew with each\nsuccessive wave of new voters."},{"time":101040,"text":"During Reconstruction,\nwhen new African-American voters,"},{"time":104000,"text":"new African-American citizens,"},{"time":106560,"text":"began to exercise their power,"},{"time":108600,"text":"they celebrated in jubilee parades"},{"time":110840,"text":"that connected emancipation\nwith their newfound right to vote."},{"time":114920,"text":"A few decades later, the suffragettes"},{"time":117680,"text":"brought a spirit\nof theatricality to their fight,"},{"time":120800,"text":"marching together in white dresses\nas they claimed the franchise."},{"time":124680,"text":"And the Civil Rights Movement,"},{"time":126240,"text":"which sought to redeem\nthe promise of equal citizenship"},{"time":129039,"text":"that had been betrayed by Jim Crow,"},{"time":131800,"text":"put voting right at the center."},{"time":134160,"text":"From Freedom Summer to the march in Selma,"},{"time":136760,"text":"that generation of activists\nknew that voting matters,"},{"time":140000,"text":"and they knew that spectacle\nand the performance of power"},{"time":143120,"text":"is key to actually claiming power."}]},{"cues":[{"time":146560,"text":"But it's been over a half century\nsince Selma and the Voting Rights Act,"},{"time":150880,"text":"and in the decades since,"},{"time":152880,"text":"this face-to-face culture of voting"},{"time":155200,"text":"has just about disappeared."},{"time":157200,"text":"It's been killed by television"},{"time":159160,"text":"and then the internet."},{"time":160720,"text":"The couch has replaced the commons."},{"time":163040,"text":"Screens have made\ncitizens into spectators."},{"time":166040,"text":"And while it's nice to share\npolitical memes on social media,"},{"time":169360,"text":"that's a rather quiet kind of citizenship."},{"time":172560,"text":"It's what the sociologist Sherry Turkle\ncalls \"being alone together.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":177360,"text":"What we need today"},{"time":178840,"text":"is an electoral culture\nthat is about being together together,"},{"time":182720,"text":"in person,"},{"time":183960,"text":"in loud and passionate ways,"},{"time":186200,"text":"so that instead of being\n\"eat your vegetables\" or \"do you duty,\""},{"time":190480,"text":"voting can feel more like \"join the club\""},{"time":193480,"text":"or, better yet, \"join the party.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":196160,"text":"Imagine if we had,\nacross the country right now,"},{"time":199720,"text":"in local places but nationwide,"},{"time":202680,"text":"a concerted effort\nto revive a face-to-face set of ways"},{"time":206360,"text":"to engage and electioneer:"},{"time":208600,"text":"outdoor shows in which candidates\nand their causes are mocked"},{"time":212480,"text":"and praised in broad satirical style;"},{"time":215200,"text":"soapbox speeches by citizens;"},{"time":217840,"text":"public debates held inside pubs;"},{"time":221920,"text":"streets filled with political art\nand handmade posters and murals;"},{"time":226680,"text":"battle of the band concerts in which\ncompeting performers rep their candidates."},{"time":232360,"text":"Now, all of this may sound\na little bit 18th century to you,"},{"time":236440,"text":"but in fact, it doesn't have to be\nany more 18th century"},{"time":239800,"text":"than, say, Broadway's \"Hamilton,\""},{"time":243040,"text":"which is to say vibrantly contemporary."}]},{"cues":[{"time":245640,"text":"And the fact is that all around the world,"},{"time":247664,"text":"today, millions of people\nare voting like this."},{"time":251280,"text":"In India, elections are colorful,\ncommunal affairs."},{"time":255560,"text":"In Brazil, election day\nis a festive, carnival-type atmosphere."},{"time":260959,"text":"In Taiwan and Hong Kong,\nthere is a spectacle,"},{"time":263480,"text":"eye-popping, eye-grabbing spectacle"},{"time":265760,"text":"to the street theater of elections."}]},{"cues":[{"time":268720,"text":"You might ask, well,\nhere in America, who has time for this?"},{"time":272480,"text":"And I would tell you"},{"time":273760,"text":"that the average American\nwatches five hours of television a day."},{"time":278240,"text":"You might ask, who has the motivation?"},{"time":280560,"text":"And I'll tell you,"},{"time":281800,"text":"any citizen who wants to be seen and heard"},{"time":285960,"text":"not as a prop, not as a talking point,"},{"time":288280,"text":"but as a participant, as a creator."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291720,"text":"Well, how do we make this happen?"},{"time":294800,"text":"Simply by making it happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296920,"text":"That's why a group of colleagues and I"},{"time":298800,"text":"launched a new project\ncalled \"The Joy of Voting.\""},{"time":302880,"text":"In four cities across the United States --"},{"time":305360,"text":"Philadelphia, Miami,"},{"time":307040,"text":"Akron, Ohio, and Wichita, Kansas --"},{"time":309520,"text":"we've gathered together\nartists and activists,"},{"time":312480,"text":"educators, political folks,\nneighbors, everyday citizens"},{"time":316240,"text":"to come together and create projects"},{"time":318000,"text":"that can foster this culture\nof voting in a local way."}]},{"cues":[{"time":322240,"text":"In Miami, that means\nall-night parties with hot DJs"},{"time":325320,"text":"where the only way to get in\nis to show that you're registered to vote."},{"time":329160,"text":"In Akron, it means political plays"},{"time":332200,"text":"being performed\nin the bed of a flatbed truck"},{"time":334760,"text":"that moves from neighborhood\nto neighborhood."},{"time":337960,"text":"In Philadelphia,"},{"time":339200,"text":"it's a voting-themed scavenger hunt\nall throughout colonial old town."},{"time":343160,"text":"And in Wichita, it's making\nmixtapes and live graffiti art"},{"time":348200,"text":"in the North End to get out the vote."},{"time":350760,"text":"There are 20 of these projects,"},{"time":352280,"text":"and they are remarkable\nin their beauty and their diversity,"},{"time":355160,"text":"and they are changing people."},{"time":356760,"text":"Let me tell you about a couple of them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358840,"text":"In Miami, we've commissioned and artist,"},{"time":360840,"text":"a young artist named Atomico,"},{"time":362880,"text":"to create some vivid and vibrant images\nfor a new series of \"I voted\" stickers."},{"time":367880,"text":"But the thing is, Atomico had never voted."},{"time":371080,"text":"He wasn't even registered."},{"time":372800,"text":"So as he got to work on creating\nthis artwork for these stickers,"},{"time":377320,"text":"he also began to get over\nhis sense of intimidation about politics."},{"time":381480,"text":"He got himself registered,"},{"time":383120,"text":"and then he got educated\nabout the upcoming primary election,"},{"time":386440,"text":"and on election day he was out there\nnot just passing out stickers,"},{"time":389760,"text":"but chatting up voters\nand encouraging people to vote,"},{"time":392360,"text":"and talking about\nthe election with passersby."}]},{"cues":[{"time":395720,"text":"In Akron, a theater company\ncalled the Wandering Aesthetics"},{"time":399520,"text":"has been putting on\nthese pickup truck plays."},{"time":402320,"text":"And to do so, they put out\nan open call to the public"},{"time":405120,"text":"asking for speeches,\nmonologues, dialogues, poems,"},{"time":408640,"text":"snippets of anything\nthat could be read aloud"},{"time":411000,"text":"and woven into a performance."},{"time":413280,"text":"They got dozens of submissions."},{"time":415720,"text":"One of them was a poem"},{"time":417640,"text":"written by nine students in an ESL class,"},{"time":420800,"text":"all of them Hispanic migrant workers"},{"time":422960,"text":"from nearby Hartville, Ohio."},{"time":425880,"text":"I want to read to you from this poem."},{"time":429200,"text":"It's called \"The Joy of Voting.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":432600,"text":"\"I would like to vote for the first time"},{"time":435040,"text":"because things are changing for Hispanics."},{"time":438000,"text":"I used to be afraid of ghosts."},{"time":440160,"text":"Now I am afraid of people."},{"time":442480,"text":"There's more violence and racism."},{"time":444960,"text":"Voting can change this."},{"time":447840,"text":"The border wall is nothing."},{"time":449800,"text":"It's just a wall."},{"time":452040,"text":"The wall of shame is something."},{"time":455800,"text":"It's very important to vote"},{"time":457720,"text":"so we can break down this wall of shame."},{"time":461320,"text":"I have passion in my heart."},{"time":463480,"text":"Voting gives me a voice and power."},{"time":466400,"text":"I can stand up and do something.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":470960,"text":"\"The Joy of Voting\" project\nisn't just about joy."},{"time":473920,"text":"It's about this passion."},{"time":475480,"text":"It's about feeling and belief,"},{"time":477840,"text":"and it isn't just our organization's work."},{"time":480560,"text":"All across this country right now,"},{"time":482520,"text":"immigrants, young people, veterans,\npeople of all different backgrounds"},{"time":485920,"text":"are coming together to create\nthis kind of passionate, joyful activity"},{"time":489440,"text":"around elections,"},{"time":490880,"text":"in red and blue states,\nin urban and rural communities,"},{"time":493840,"text":"people of every political background."},{"time":495960,"text":"What they have in common is simply this:"},{"time":498680,"text":"their work is rooted in place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":502320,"text":"Because remember,\nall citizenship is local."},{"time":505720,"text":"When politics becomes\njust a presidential election,"},{"time":509280,"text":"we yell and we scream at our screens,\nand then we collapse, exhausted."},{"time":513679,"text":"But when politics is about us"},{"time":517320,"text":"and our neighbors\nand other people in our community"},{"time":520120,"text":"coming together to create experiences\nof collective voice and imagination,"},{"time":525440,"text":"then we begin to remember\nthat this stuff matters."},{"time":528560,"text":"We begin to remember\nthat this is the stuff of self-government."}]},{"cues":[{"time":533240,"text":"Which brings me back to where I began."},{"time":535880,"text":"Why bother?"},{"time":537640,"text":"There's one way to answer this question."},{"time":540440,"text":"Voting matters because it is\na self-fulfilling act of belief."},{"time":545440,"text":"It feeds the spirit of mutual interest\nthat makes any society thrive."},{"time":550960,"text":"When we vote, even if it is in anger,"},{"time":553640,"text":"we are part of a collective,\ncreative leap of faith."},{"time":557840,"text":"Voting helps us generate\nthe very power that we wish we had."}]},{"cues":[{"time":562240,"text":"It's no accident\nthat democracy and theater"},{"time":565080,"text":"emerged around the same time\nin ancient Athens."},{"time":568200,"text":"Both of them yank the individual\nout of the enclosure of her private self."},{"time":573440,"text":"Both of them create great\npublic experiences of shared ritual."},{"time":578200,"text":"Both of them bring the imagination to life"},{"time":580760,"text":"in ways that remind us\nthat all of our bonds in the end"},{"time":584080,"text":"are imagined, and can be reimagined."}]},{"cues":[{"time":590760,"text":"This moment right now,"},{"time":592800,"text":"when we think about\nthe meaning of imagination,"},{"time":596240,"text":"is so fundamentally important,"},{"time":600480,"text":"and our ability to take that spirit"},{"time":603680,"text":"and to take that sense"},{"time":605280,"text":"that there is something greater out there,"},{"time":607360,"text":"is not just a matter\nof technical expertise."},{"time":611160,"text":"It's not just a matter of making the time\nor having the know-how."},{"time":614240,"text":"It is a matter of spirit."}]},{"cues":[{"time":616720,"text":"But let me give you an answer\nto this question, \"Why bother?\""},{"time":619680,"text":"that is maybe a little less spiritual\nand a bit more pointed."},{"time":624440,"text":"Why bother voting?"},{"time":626240,"text":"Because there is\nno such thing as not voting."},{"time":629160,"text":"Not voting is voting,"},{"time":631000,"text":"for everything that you\nmay detest and oppose."},{"time":633920,"text":"Not voting can be dressed up"},{"time":635680,"text":"as an act of principled,\npassive resistance,"},{"time":638720,"text":"but in fact not voting"},{"time":640680,"text":"is actively handing power over"},{"time":642920,"text":"to those whose interests\nare counter to your own,"},{"time":645280,"text":"and those who would be very glad\nto take advantage of your absence."},{"time":648840,"text":"Not voting is for suckers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":652800,"text":"Imagine where this country would be"},{"time":654520,"text":"if all the folks who in 2010\ncreated the Tea Party"},{"time":657640,"text":"had decided that,\nyou know, politics is too messy,"},{"time":660600,"text":"voting is too complicated."},{"time":661880,"text":"There is no possibility\nof our votes adding up to anything."},{"time":665320,"text":"They didn't preemptively\nsilence themselves."},{"time":667640,"text":"They showed up,"},{"time":669440,"text":"and in the course of showing up,\nthey changed American politics."},{"time":673480,"text":"Imagine if all of the followers\nof Donald Trump and Bernie Sanders"},{"time":678280,"text":"had decided not to upend\nthe political status quo"},{"time":682000,"text":"and blow apart the frame\nof the previously possible"},{"time":685080,"text":"in American politics."},{"time":686720,"text":"They did that by voting."}]},{"cues":[{"time":691160,"text":"We live in a time right now,"},{"time":693400,"text":"divided, often very dark,"},{"time":695960,"text":"where across the left and the right,\nthere's a lot of talk of revolution"},{"time":699600,"text":"and the need for revolution\nto disrupt everyday democracy."},{"time":703120,"text":"Well, here's the thing:"},{"time":704760,"text":"everyday democracy already\ngives us a playbook for revolution."},{"time":708760,"text":"In the 2012 presidential election,"},{"time":710840,"text":"young voters, Latino voters,"},{"time":712600,"text":"Asian-American voters, low-income voters,"},{"time":714880,"text":"all showed up at less than 50 percent."},{"time":719200,"text":"In the 2014 midterm elections,\nturnout was 36 percent,"},{"time":723280,"text":"which was a 70-year low."},{"time":725920,"text":"And in your average local election,"},{"time":727840,"text":"turnout hovers\nsomewhere around 20 percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":731320,"text":"I invite you to imagine 100 percent."},{"time":735640,"text":"Picture 100 percent."},{"time":738080,"text":"Mobilize 100 percent,"},{"time":740240,"text":"and overnight, we get revolution."},{"time":743040,"text":"Overnight, the policy priorities\nof this country change dramatically,"},{"time":747080,"text":"and every level of government\nbecomes radically more responsive"},{"time":750640,"text":"to all the people."},{"time":753240,"text":"What would it take\nto mobilize 100 percent?"},{"time":756480,"text":"Well, we do have to push back\nagainst efforts afoot"},{"time":759040,"text":"all across the country right now"},{"time":760800,"text":"to make voting harder."},{"time":762480,"text":"But at the same time,"},{"time":764000,"text":"we have to actively create\na positive culture of voting"},{"time":767160,"text":"that people want to belong to,"},{"time":768800,"text":"be part of, and experience together."},{"time":771360,"text":"We have to make purpose."},{"time":773000,"text":"We have to make joy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775160,"text":"So yes, let's have that revolution,"},{"time":777840,"text":"a revolution of spirit, of ideas,"},{"time":780360,"text":"of policy and participation,"},{"time":782400,"text":"a revolution against cynicism,"},{"time":784560,"text":"a revolution against the self-fulfilling\nsense of powerlessness."},{"time":788520,"text":"Let's vote this revolution into existence,"},{"time":791880,"text":"and while we're at it,"},{"time":793240,"text":"let's have some fun."}]},{"cues":[{"time":794800,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":796040,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}